collection.description: This collection features our conversations throughout the State of Maine held with educators, students, community members, and major Maine industry professionals. We are asking what youth will need to thrive personally, civically, and economically in the Maine of 2050. The collection is expanding daily, so check back!
collection.title: Maine ED 2050

highlights.description: The benefits of experiential learning opportunities
The importance of taking individual circumstances into account
A good life is knowing who you are and the role you can play in your community.
Youth don't want to play the "standard game." They are more determined to align their career path with their values and interests than in years past.
Youth are accepting but this may lead to lower levels of agency.
Youth have less hope for their ability to play a meaningful role in the changes society needs.
Youth are spending more time on phones and less time in person with each other, but they seem more open minded and more likely to cross groups to be friends.
Youth have resilience and a new set of skills to deal with uncertainty.
